</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-45_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>The Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 require UK employers to provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure employees receive immediate attention if injured or taken ill at work. This regulation extends to settings like schools and daycares, where it is crucial to have staff trained in paediatric first aid.



